---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About & Provenance" description="Where Palestra AI comes from — the schools, the pilot, the numbers, and how this platform came to be.">
  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">About &amp; provenance</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold text-navy-950 md:text-5xl">Where this comes from</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-navy-700">
      Palestra AI started as a two-year pilot (AY 2024/25 – 2025/26) across schools in
      Avola, Sicily — <em>"L'Intelligenza Artificiale spiegata dai ragazzi ai bambini"</em>
      (AI explained by teenagers to children). This platform is jointly developed to
      carry that methodology forward.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Schools -->
  <section class="section border-t border-navy-100">
    <p class="eyebrow">The school network</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950">Avola, Sicily</h2>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900">IC G. Bianca</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-700">
          Primary school partner. Host of the Four Stations delivery and the
          19 May 2026 closing event, with formal partnership convention in place.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900">IC Capuana–De Amicis</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-700">
          Second primary partner in the Avola network, part of the two-year pilot
          cohort.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="font-bold text-navy-900">Liceo Majorana (IISS Majorana)</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-700">
          Secondary partner — home of the Teenager Circle co-educators (cohorts 3A,
          4E, 5A in AY 2025/26), engaged through PCTO / Formazione Scuola Lavoro.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Numbers -->
  <section class="section border-t border-navy-100">
    <p class="eyebrow">Phase I, by the numbers</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950">A pilot already run, not a plan</h2>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
      <div class="card text-center">
        <p class="stat">~400</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-navy-600">primary pupils across the two-year pilot</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card text-center">
        <p class="stat">~150</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-navy-600">Liceo Majorana co-educators (~80 + ~70 across two cohorts)</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card text-center">
        <p class="stat">16</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-navy-600">classes (quinte), 3 upper-secondary tracks involved</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card text-center">
        <p class="stat">23</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-navy-600">stories produced and catalogued (3A storytelling cohort)</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card border-orange-200">
        <p class="stat">61%</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-700">
          of pupils named <em>"il successo non è solo vincere"</em> (success is not only
          about winning) as the lesson they remembered — the single largest
          concept-recall figure of the entire POST evaluation, 19 May 2026.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-orange-200">
        <p class="stat">1 in 3</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-700">
          pupils independently formulated <em>"l'IA può sbagliare i disegni"</em> (AI
          can get the drawings wrong) during the Comic-Strip Review station — what we
          call <strong>Human-in-the-Loop a 10 anni</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-navy-400">
      Source: POST evaluation, IC Bianca, 19 May 2026. Station-level ratings: Talento
      71%, Valore 72%, Successo 78%, Comic-Strip Review 64% "tantissimo".
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- 19 May event -->
  <section class="section border-t border-navy-100">
    <div class="card bg-navy-950 text-navy-50 md:flex md:items-center md:justify-between md:gap-8">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-400">Closing event — 19 May 2026</p>
        <h3 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-white">Una Palestra per allenare la mente, il cuore e il futuro</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-sm text-navy-200">
          The Phase I pilot closed with a public event at IC Bianca — families,
          institutions, the Liceo Majorana co-educators and the primary pupils
          together, presenting the stories, the stations, and the POST results
          summarised above.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-navy-400">
      Photo and video material from the 19 May event is treated with care: imagery of
      identifiable minors is reviewed before any public or platform use, separate from
      its authorised use at the in-person event.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder / ownership -->
  <section class="section border-t border-navy-100">
    <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Founder</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-bold text-navy-950">Marcello Vinci</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-navy-700">
          INSEAD Executive MBA, engineer, certified BIM Manager. Palestra AI is not a
          commercial edtech product — it is a methodological architecture introducing
          generative AI into education as a medium for human formation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">This platform</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-bold text-navy-950">Jointly developed</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-navy-700">
          This prototype is part of a research collaboration between Palestra AI and
          INSEAD for Phase II (AY 2026/27). Ownership and governance structures will be
          formalised separately — what matters here is showing how the methodology
          translates into a usable platform across the four levels.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
